CHOLERA - KENYA (03)
********************
A ProMED-mail Post
See Also
Cholera - Kenya 970917161726
Cholera - Kenya (02) 971022000330
Date: Wed, 22 Oct 1997
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: The Nation, Nairobi 21 Oct 1997

The spread of cholera continues as 3 more deaths have occurred in the
Muhoroni division, which has seen 25 deaths in the past 2 months.
Nationwide, there have been 140-300 cases and 140 deaths. The worst hit
areas are Migori, Suba, Homa Bay, Rachuonyo and Kisumu districts in Nyanza
Province.
Medecins sans Frontieres, World Vision and the Red Cross Society are
involved in helping to fight the epidemic.
[As mentioned in an earlier posting, ProMED-mail would very much like to
receive an update from knowledgeable sources in Kenya concerning details of
this epidemic. - Mod. PC
--
Dorothy Preslar
